This sample shows how you can create a screensaver using an animated image.

The spinning ball animation is a transparent PNG image (with alpha channel) composed of 6 frames. The ball scale is proportional to screen (its size will increase automatically if the screen is larger than 640x480). The background is a screen snapshot (75% darken).
This sample done by Axialis Software is copyright free (except the background music, see below) and can be used as a template to make your own screensaver.

The background music is a loop sound (short sound which can be played in loop to create an endless music). This sound have been resampled to low quality (12.000 kHz, 8 Bit, Stereo) for demo purpose.
